.SH NAME
.PP
git smga
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
git smga command - iterate over submodules and current directory to
execute git command
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
git smga is a helper alias to execute git commands in each submodule.
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP \[bu] 2
git smga status
.IP \[bu] 2
git smga \[lq]remote -v\[rq]
.SH SEE ALSO
.PP
smf smfa smg
.SH DETAILS
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
smga = \[dq]!f() { : git man smga; \[rs]
    [ $# -ne 1 ] && echo \[aq]Usage: smga command\[aq] && return; \[rs]
    $SHELL -c \[rs]\[dq]git $\[at]\[rs]\[dq]; \[rs]
    git smg \[rs]\[dq]$\[at]\[rs]\[dq]; \[rs]
}; f\[dq]
\f[R]
.fi
